THOUGHT

ROOT CAUSE: `src/be_code.c:455-465` in `exp2reg()` materializes conditional/not expressions into `e->v.idx`, which may be the source operand register, even when the caller provided an explicit destination register. For `var j = !i`, `code_not()` does not emit a real unary opcode; it marks the `ETLOCAL` expression `i` as a delayed boolean conditional (`e->not = NOT_EXPR | NOT_MASK`) while leaving `e->v.idx == 0`. Later `be_code_setvar()` calls `exp2reg(finfo, &e2, e1->v.idx)` with destination register 1 for the new local `j`, but `exp2reg()` first calls `var2reg()`, which returns the existing local register 0, then ignores the requested destination and emits `LDBOOL R0 ...`. The generated bytecode proves this: `JMPF R0`, `LDBOOL R0 false`, `LDBOOL R0 true`, `MOVE R1 R0`; so computing `!i` overwrites `i`, and `return i` returns `false` instead of `1`. This is why `tests/bool.be` fails at `assert(f(1) == 1)`.

LOCAL FIX: In `exp2reg()`, when a conditional expression has to be materialized and the caller supplied a concrete destination register, use that destination rather than `e->v.idx`. Ensure it is allocated when it is the current free register, and update the expression descriptor to point to the destination before emitting the boolean loads. Minimal replacement:

```diff
diff --git a/src/be_code.c b/src/be_code.c
--- a/src/be_code.c
+++ b/src/be_code.c
@@
 static int exp2reg(bfuncinfo *finfo, bexpdesc *e, int dst)
 {
     int reg = var2reg(finfo, e, dst);
     if (hasjump(e)) { /* if conditional expression */
         int pcf = NO_JUMP;  /* position of an eventual LOAD false */
         int pct = NO_JUMP;  /* position of an eventual LOAD true */
         int jpt = appendjump(finfo, jumpboolop(e, 1), e);
-        reg = e->v.idx;
+        if (dst >= 0) {
+            reg = dst;
+            if (reg == finfo->freereg) {
+                be_code_allocregs(finfo, 1);
+            }
+            e->type = ETREG;
+            e->v.idx = reg;
+        } else {
+            reg = e->v.idx;
+        }
         be_code_conjump(finfo, &e->t, jpt);
         pcf = code_bool(finfo, reg, 0, 1);
         pct = code_bool(finfo, reg, 1, 0);
```

For `var j = !i`, this generates the boolean result in `R1`, preserving `R0`.

GLOBAL FIX: Separate "place" expressions (locals/upvalues/members that name storage) from "value/result" expressions in the compiler IR/codegen API. A delayed boolean expression should carry an explicit destination/result slot or be converted to an rvalue before assignment; it should not reuse the source variable's register implicitly. Concretely, replace `exp2reg(finfo, e, dst)`/`var2reg()` mutation semantics with APIs like `materialize_value(expr, dst)` and `address_of_assignable(expr)`, assert that materializing an rvalue never writes to an `ETLOCAL` source unless `dst == source` by explicit request, and add bytecode-generation unit tests that dump/execute cases such as `var y = !x; return x`, `var y = x == 1; return x`, and conditional assignments from locals. This design-level separation prevents an entire class of bugs where expression materialization accidentally clobbers the storage being read.

